## 3. Three-Tab Design Philosophy

### Why Three Overarching Tabs?

| Benefit | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Separation of Concerns** | Chat for conversation, SQL for technical review, Charts for visualization |
| **Audit Trail** | All SQLs visible in one place for compliance review |
| **Comparison** | Easy to compare multiple SQLs or charts side-by-side |
| **Workspace Feel** | SQL Tab = SQL Workbench, Chart Tab = Mini Dashboard |
| **Non-Disruptive** | Review SQL without losing chat scroll position |

### ID Correlation System

Every answer generates correlated artifacts:

```
Question Asked
     │
     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Message (msg-123)                                  │
│  ├── content: "Here are your top 10 loans..."      │
│  ├── sqlId: "sql-456"  ─────────► SQL Tab item     │
│  └── chartId: "chart-789" ──────► Chart Tab item   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

This enables:
- Click "View SQL" in Answer tab → Jump to SQL tab, auto-scroll to sql-456
- Click "View Chart" in Answer tab → Jump to Chart tab, auto-scroll to chart-789
- Click question link in SQL tab → Jump back to Answer tab, scroll to msg-123

